OL,6,FBased on statistics from the NSPCC, in
OL,7,Fthe UK, at least one child is killed
OL,8,Feach week because of abuse or neglect.
OL,10,FBetween 2022 and 2023, 74 children
OL,11,Fwere killed by confirmed offences of
OL,12,Fmurder, manslaughter and infanticide.
OL,14,FThese killings are most commonly
OL,15,Fcaused by the child's parent or
OL,16,Fstepparent.
OL,18,FBut because there was no trial into
OL,19,FShay's death, it is unknown whether
OL,20,Fabuse or neglect played a part.
